Series Name: Data from database: World Development Indicators

Country Code: GNI per capita is gross national income divided by midyear population. GNI (formerly GNP) is the sum of value added by all resident producers plus any product taxes (less subsidies) not included in the valuation of output plus net receipts of primary income (compensation of employees and property income) from abroad. Data are in constant 2015 U.S. dollars.
1990 [YR1990]: World Bank national accounts data, and OECD National Accounts data files.
2000 [YR2000]: Economic Policy & Debt: National accounts: US$ at constant 2015 prices: Aggregate indicators

Country Code: GDP per capita is gross domestic product divided by midyear population. GDP is the sum of gross value added by all resident producers in the economy plus any product taxes and minus any subsidies not included in the value of the products. It is calculated without making deductions for depreciation of fabricated assets or for depletion and degradation of natural resources. Data are in constant 2015 U.S. dollars.
1990 [YR1990]: World Bank national accounts data, and OECD National Accounts data files.
2000 [YR2000]: Economic Policy & Debt: National accounts: US$ at constant 2015 prices: Aggregate indicators
